# BROWSER-restack.md - Substack Restack Patterns

## SS 10. Restack with a Note

🚨 **Radix UI dropdown:** Substack uses Radix UI for the Restack menu. `.click()` and `MouseEvent('click')` do NOT open it. MUST use `PointerEvent` sequence (`pointerdown` → `pointerup` → `click`) — this is how Radix triggers state changes.

🚨 **Find button by `aria-label="Restack"`**, NOT by `innerText`. The button text is the restack count number (e.g. "7"), not "Restack".

### Step 1 — Click Restack button and select "Restack with a note"

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button[aria-label="Restack"]'));
    var targetBtn = btns[${noteIndex}];
    if (!targetBtn) return { error: 'restack button not found at index ' + ${noteIndex} };
    // Radix UI requires pointer events to open dropdown
    var rect = targetBtn.getBoundingClientRect();
    var cx = rect.x + rect.width / 2, cy = rect.y + rect.height / 2;
    targetBtn.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointerdown', { bubbles: true, clientX: cx, clientY: cy }));
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 50));
    targetBtn.dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent('pointerup', { bubbles: true, clientX: cx, clientY: cy }));
    targetBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, clientX: cx, clientY: cy }));
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));
    // Menu opens in Radix portal
    var menuItems = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[role="menuitem"]'));
    var quoteItem = menuItems.find(m => m.innerText.trim() === 'Restack with a note');
    if (!quoteItem) return { error: 'menu not opened', state: targetBtn.getAttribute('data-state'), items: menuItems.map(m => m.innerText.trim()) };
    quoteItem.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000));
    var dialog = document.querySelector('[role="dialog"]');
    var editor = dialog ? dialog.querySelector('[contenteditable="true"]') : null;
    return { opened: !!editor };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Step 2 — Type quote note and post

Use **BROWSER-note.md SS 9 Step 2** (identical Notes composer — contenteditable + "Post" button).

### When to Restack

Restack content aligned with your pillars with genuine {{role}} perspective. Skip off-topic, low-quality, self-restacks. Quote note: 1-3 sentences adding real value, not just "great post".
